    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-upside lineup anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.67) and **Kyle Tucker** (77.10), both of whom benefit significantly from favorable weather conditions and high-leverage spots in the order. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** finds the most advantageous matchup, facing an exploitable arm in Kochanowicz (5.35 xERA), with wind-aided conditions pushing his production profile into the elite tier. While **Kyle Tucker** possesses a similarly strong projection, managers must monitor the 42% rain risk in his contest; should the weather shift, we have sufficient depth to pivot. We are also leaning heavily on the platoon advantage today, particularly with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), who grades out as a premier start against the vulnerable arm of R. L\u00f3pez. His efficiency is bolstered by his #2 spot in the order and a significant platoon boost, making him a cornerstone of today's scoring potential.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Marcell Ozuna** (59.22), whose efficiency was strong enough to warrant a start on most days but ultimately fell just short of the high-floor options we prioritized in the UTIL and corner infield spots. While **Marcell Ozuna** offers clear home run upside, the optimizer favored the balanced efficiency of **Nolan Schanuel** (60.14) and the strategic platoon alignment of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Nasim Nunez**. Elsewhere, **Jackson Merrill** (70.77) remains a high-confidence play, as he maximizes a significant park factor and a favorable matchup against J. Herget. Conversely, we are playing it cautious with **Heliot Ramos** (41.44); he makes the lineup due to his speed profile and our organizational emphasis on SB, but his low score reflects a difficult matchup against a top-tier arm in Yamamoto and the same looming rain risk that threatens **Kyle Tucker**.",
